    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Ideas so far:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- It seems that using logarithm of the age may be a good idea\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- We might rescale other covariates to avoid big numbers for numerical stability\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- We might include the birth weight as target variable values at the age 0. Then if we take logarithm, we first add +1 to all age values.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Rahul\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Just for numerical stabalization we can also put log on weight, or any other down scaling transformation eg Standardization, Normalization.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"also these tranformations make the relation pretty linear.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
